replies.body:
When you buy {{item:3053}} or{{item:3022}} you still get the full benefit, even when you don't farm {{item:3052}} 

What OP is saying is that you pay 1200 gold for {{item:3052}} , which gives garbage stats. To put this into perspective, {{item:3052}} gives you 150 health (which you can stack up to total 300 health) and 15 AD for 1200 gold. {{item:1011}} gives you 380 health for 1000 gold.

So you get less than half as much health than you would if you bought {{item:1011}} , which is actually cheaper, and when you finally finish stacking (which, if you stay in lane AND get perfect cs, takes about 3 minutes), you still have less health than {{item:1011}}
